<subSubSection pageId="391" pageNumber="392" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="391" pageNumber="392">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="391" pageNumber="392">
This species inhabits the North American Cordilleras from the arctic circle in eastern Alaska and west-central Yukon Territory (Lindroth 1963b: 392) south to San Bernardino County in southeastern California (Dajoz 2007: 20, as 
<taxonomicName class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="391" pageNumber="392" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="convexiuscula">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="391" pageNumber="392">Bembidion convexiuscula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), northern Idaho (Hatch 1953: 94), northwestern Wyoming (Teton County, UASM), and east-central Montana (Russell 1968: 57).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
